
[1]sealing-wax

   SE'ALING-WAX, n. [seal and wax.] A compound of gum lac and the red oxyd
   of mercury; used for fastening a folded letter and thus consealing the
   writing, and for receiving impressions of seals set to instruments.
   Sealing wax is hard or soft, and may be of any color.
